      "span_text": "This has two important implications with respect to methods utilizing release of ceramide prior to the assay [CITATION_3] ): (i) important information about GSL lipoforms, with possible implications for differential processing, and possibly even cellular origins, may be lost and (ii) incorporating iGb 3 occurring in one or a few lipoforms into a larger pool of Gb 3 encompassing a broader range of lipoforms, by removing the ceramide moieties, could actually serve to dilute the overall iGb 3 signal rather than enhance it."
